    "claim": "The pool reduces `totalLiquidity` whenever assets are sent to the orderbook, but it does not track the outbound amount as a receivable. Because `provideLiquidity` mints new LP shares against the reduced `pool.totalLiquidity`, a user who deposits while orders are outstanding can buy into the pool at a discount and receive a pro-rata claim on assets that were financed entirely by earlier LPs.",
    "impact": "Incumbent LPs can be heavily diluted. An attacker can wait until the orderbook has pulled most of a pool's assets, deposit a small amount, then capture a disproportionate share of later orderbook repayments and recovered inventory when withdrawing.",
